Inferior portion of the broad ligament containing the ovarian vessels","Lateral portion of the broad ligament containing the round ligament","Superior portion of the broad ligament containing the fallopian tube"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Esuperior portion of the broad ligament containing the fallopian tube\u003C/strong\u003E describes the mesosalpinx. This double-layered fold of peritoneum suspends and supports the fallopian tube, carrying its blood vessels and nerves.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Einferior portion of the broad ligament containing the ovarian vessels\u003C/strong\u003E is the mesovarium. The \u003Cstrong\u003Ecentral portion of the broad ligament containing the uterine vessels\u003C/strong\u003E describes the parametrium. The \u003Cstrong\u003Elateral portion of the broad ligament containing the round ligament\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect as the round ligament runs in the anterior leaf of the broad ligament. The \u003Cstrong\u003Eposterior portion of the broad ligament containing the ovary\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect as the ovary projects through the posterior surface of the broad ligament.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The mesosalpinx is a fold of peritoneum that suspends the fallopian tube within the broad ligament of the uterus.","The mesosalpinx forms the superior portion of the broad ligament, which contains blood vessels and nerves that supply the fallopian tube."],"references":["Evans, T. J., \u0026 Ganjam, V. K. (2017). Reproductive anatomy and physiology. In Reproductive and Developmental Toxicology (pp. 7-37). Academic Press.","Cheng LK, O\u0027Grady G, Du P, Egbuji JU, Windsor JA, Pullan AJ. Gastrointestinal system. Wiley Interdiscip Rev Syst Biol Med. 2010 Jan-Feb;2(1):65-79. doi: 10.1002/wsbm.19. PMID: 20836011; PMCID: PMC4221587","Kahai P, Mandiga P, Wehrle CJ, Lobo S. Anatomy, Abdomen and Pelvis: Larg